public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/rooms-to-go/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/dinah-sutton-photography/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/interceramic/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/stag-partners/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/nothing-bundt-cakes/public"}],"shortDescription":null,"metaDescription":null,"altTexts":null,"jsonLd":null,"_migration":{"scrapedAt":"2026-03-06T13:32:09.416Z","source":"wordpress-xml-export","wpPostDate":"2018-05-13 17:29:19","wpCategories":["Meet the Kids"],"wpTags":["2018","Accessible Bathroom","Dream Bedroom"],"thumbnailId":7235,"needsReview":[],"cfHeroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/69a269e0-9112-4ca5-a482-d8ebdab2aa00/full"},"streamVideoId":"ae74451b60a54d7428ed5fbbb62e9ad5","roomCount":2}');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('anna', 'Anna', 2015, 'completed', 0, 1, 1, '{"name":"Anna","slug":"anna","year":2015,"status":"completed","bio":"Anna is an eleven-year old little girl who was born in 2004 after a seemingly normal pregnancy.  She seemed like a normal newborn until she was six weeks old when she started having seizures while she was sleeping.  It was also apparent that she wasn''t achieving most of her milestones on time.  Doctors began a round of seemingly endless genetic tests and didn''t receive an answer until she was eight months old when she was diagnosed with mitochondrial disease.    Mitochondrial disease is a genetic disorder where the body can''t produce enough energy to sustain all of its bodily functions properly.  The disease affects people in different ways and severity depending on where the genetic defect is located. In Anna''s case it affects her neurological and muscular development.  She is nonverbal, has low muscular tone, global developmental delays and is dependent on her parents for all of her care.  Her parents also have to be extremely careful when she gets sick because her body takes longer to recover.   Through the years Anna has made great strides with the help of physical therapy, occupational therapy, aquatic therapy and music therapy.  She can play independently with small hand toys and can walk short distances with assistance.  Her seizures are thankfully controlled with medication and her general physical growth has been very good.     Anna has an amazing smile and laugh that lights up the room.  Anna''s parents prefer to consider her a happy little girl who just happens to have a genetic disorder and, despite her challenges, it does not define her.   She participates in the Miracle League softball team and attends Alpharetta Elementary School which has an amazing special needs program.  She lives at home with a 7-year old sister and 4-year old brother. Her sister loves cheering on Anna during physical therapy and helps her parents give Anna her medications.   Jason and Gwen handle the challenges of Anna''s needs and therapies despite having difficult careers.  Both Jason and Gwen are police officers in the metro Atlanta area and have balanced the needs of their three kids despite unusual schedules and the stressful nature of their jobs.  Jason has been with the City of Dunwoody police department since its inception 6 years ago and also served 10 years with the Cobb County Police Department.  Gwen has been with the City of Marietta police department for 14 years.   The wheelchair accessible bathroom will be a huge help for Anna''s parents who struggle because Anna has become to heavy to lift into the bathtub.  ","quote":"Anna is an eleven-year old little girl who was born in 2004 after a seemingly normal pregnancy.  She seemed like a normal newborn until she was six weeks old when she started having seizures while she was sleeping.  It was also apparent that she wasn''t achieving most of her milestones on time.  Doct","heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/hero/public","roomTypes":[],"photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/hero/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/sims/hero/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/abby/photo-48/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/photo-04/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/photo-05/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/photo-06/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/photo-07/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/photo-08/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anna/photo-09/public","alt":"Anna makeover photo"}],"age":null,"diagnosis":null,"_migration":{"cfHeroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/c1469825-32af-423f-7786-0e0f7cc1fb00/full","source":"wix-migration","wixNumber":34},"roomCount":1}');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('anthony-jr-and-lyric', 'Anthony Jr. & Lyric', 2023, 'completed', 0, 2, 2, '{"name":"Anthony Jr. & Lyric","slug":"anthony-jr-and-lyric","age":6,"diagnosis":"Quad Cerebal Palsy, Epilepsy, Autism","roomTypes":["Accessible Bathroom","Dream Bedroom"],"year":2023,"status":"completed","bio":"Anthony Jr. was born on December 15, 2005. He has cerebral palsy and epilepsy caused by brain-damaged experienced during a complicated and difficult birth.  Anthony is non-verbal and wheelchair-dependent.  He is a vibrant child and loves his family.  Anthony enjoys music which is no surprise since he comes from a musical family.  \n\nDespite all of Anthony Jr.''s challenges he can communicate and enjoys a good laugh.  He shows a love for life and what it means to fully live in the moment.  Anthony Jr.''s love for life also keeps his entire family going.\n\nLyric, younger brother to Anthony Jr., was born on December 11, 2015. Lyric was diagnosed with autism in 2017.  He is an extremely intelligent little boy and continues to amaze everyone with what he knows.  He enjoys music just like his older brother, Anthony Jr.  Lyric also enjoys being outdoors and interacting with people.  \n\nLyric faces challenges every day and he works really hard to do his best. He is always the energy in the room that encourages others to be ok in moments of darkness. He is such a loving little boy just like Anthony Jr.  Lyric tries his hardest to help his big brother.  He watches others take care of Anthony Jr. and attempts to mimic their actions. \n\nLyric is truly what helps Anthony Jr. continue to smile! Lyric and Anthony Jr. represent brotherly love like no others!","quote":"\"He is always the energy in the room that encourages others to be ok in moments of darkness.\"","heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/hero/public","photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-01/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-02/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-03/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-04/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-05/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-06/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-07/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-08/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-09/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-10/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-11/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-12/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-13/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-14/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-15/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-16/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-17/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/anthony-jr-and-lyric/photo-18/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmf