-06T13:32:09.447Z","source":"wordpress-xml-export","wpPostDate":"2021-06-16 23:09:00","wpCategories":["Meet the Kids"],"wpTags":["2019","Accessible Bathroom","Dream Bedroom"],"thumbnailId":1288,"needsReview":[],"cfHeroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/2ac08526-ebf5-417e-8d31-8b993321fb00/full"},"streamVideoId":"6befedea2a9571699cefdd4ec1c18f83","roomCount":2}');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('gavin', 'Gavin', 2013, 'completed', 0, 1, 1, '{"name":"Gavin","slug":"gavin","year":2013,"status":"completed","bio":"Meet 4 year old Gavin Self.  An episode in November 2010 proved a startling and life changing event for Gavin, as well as his parents and sister. As she did every evening, Gavin''s mom went into his room to kiss him goodnight and found him sitting straight up in bed shaking all over. It looked as if he was convulsing. He was initially diagnosed with a seizure disorder and put on anti-seizure medication. After a year punctuated with doctor''s appointments, spinal taps, MRI, CT scans and finally a muscle biopsy, Gavin was diagnosed with Mitochondrial Disease and severe Ataxia.  Mitochondrial Disease is progressive and Gavin struggles with it daily. A brave fighter, he currently goes to occupational, physical and speech therapy 4-5 days a week and takes half a dozen different medications. His ataxia does subside while he sleeps, but occasional gross muscle spasms during the night have caused his parents to take turns sleeping with him.   The Makeover  Sunshine on a Ranney Day came to the rescue and gave Gavin his very own baseball bedroom with custom made safe bed so he does not have to sleep in his parents’ room anymore.  We also made over his sister Addison''s room, and finished off their basement to create a space where Gavin can do his therapy, his dad can watch football, and his mom and sister can do crafts.  We wanted to give them a space where Gavin was safe, they could all be together and still have their own space.","quote":"Meet 4 year old Gavin Self.  An episode in November 2010 proved a startling and life changing event for Gavin, as well as his parents and sister. As she did every evening, Gavin''s mom went into his room to kiss him goodnight and found him sitting straight up in bed shaking all over. It looked as if ","heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/hero/public","roomTypes":[],"photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/hero/public","alt":"Gavin makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/photo-02/public","alt":"Gavin makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/photo-03/public","alt":"Gavin makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/photo-04/public","alt":"Gavin makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/photo-05/public","alt":"Gavin makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/photo-06/public","alt":"Gavin makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/gavin/photo-07/public","alt":"Gavin makeover photo"}],"age":null,"diagnosis":null,"_migration":{"cfHeroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/361fea98-cdab-4f0d-3c68-c0e653d58600/full","source":"wix-migration","wixNumber":4},"roomCount":1}');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('georgia', 'Georgia', 2018, 'completed', 0, 1, 2, '{"name":"Georgia","slug":"georgia","age":15,"diagnosis":"Cerebral Palsy, motor control issues","roomTypes":["Accessible Bathroom","Dream Bedroom"],"year":2018,"status":"completed","bio":"Georgia was born on July 26th, 2002 in Ashville, NC at 31 weeks and she weighed just 3lbs 14oz.  It was November before she was ready to leave the hospital.  Shortly after she was born she was diagnosed with Cerebral Palsy and the doctor said she would probably never walk. Georgia had great determination and worked hard and started walking at 2 years old.  She had a miniature shopping cart that she used to hold herself up and walk with and she placed her toys in the cart and pushed it all over the house.  As she learned to walk, her family would sing  \"Just put one foot in front of the other\" to her.\n\nAt the age of 4, doctors decided to try tendon lengthening surgery on her legs.  Unfortunately, it was a devastating set back and it was two years before she walked again.  Using her great drive and determination, Georgia eventually walked thru the house using only the walls to support her, but she suffered a fall and twisted her knee.  Now she must have assistance to walk anywhere whether it is using her walker or with the help of her Paw Paw.\n\nGeorgia is a very outgoing person that makes friends easily and she has the kind of smile that lights up a room when she enters it.  Growing up her favorite movies included Barbie and all the Olson Twins and she loved playing with dolls.  Now she is into her cat Molly Star who loves to come in her room to play and sleep on her bed.\n\nGeorgia started high school this year but it was rough because her classes where on opposite sides of the school.  Due to a more recent fall, she is on the Homebound program and the teacher comes to her three times a week.  It is unclear when Georgia will be able to return to school.\n\nGeorgia''s family has been blessed by her coming into their lives and thank God for her everyday.  One of her future goals is to learn to drive.  She likes watching and posting videos on You Tube and other streaming shows.  Each day is a challenge for her to stand and walk, but with her drive and determination, her family is sure she will be back up and walking soon.","quote":"\"Each day is a challenge for her to stand and walk, but with her drive and determination, her family is sure she will be back up and walking soon.\"","heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/hero/public","photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-01/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-02/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-03/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-04/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-05/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-06/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-07/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-08/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-09/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-10/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-11/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-12/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-13/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-14/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-15/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-16/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-17/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-18/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-19/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-20/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-21/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-22/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-23/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-24/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-25/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/caleb/photo-35/public","alt":"Georgia makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/abby/photo-40/public","alt":"Georgia makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/kalen/hero/public","alt":"Georgia makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/amir/photo-33/public","alt":"Georgia makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/georgia/photo-30/public","alt":"Georgia makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/sims/hero/public","alt":"Georgia makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jack/hero/public","alt":"Georgia makeover photo"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/caliyah/photo-29/public","alt":"Georgia makeove