INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('john-and-joseph', 'John & Joseph', 2023, 'completed', 0, 2, 2, '{"name":"John & Joseph","slug":"john-and-joseph","age":9,"diagnosis":"MECP2 Duplication Syndrome","roomTypes":["Accessible Bathroom","Dream Bedroom"],"year":2023,"status":"completed","bio":"John and Joseph are brothers born 16 months apart with MECP2 Duplication Syndrome or M2DS. This rare genetic condition causes many issues such as severe intellectual disabilities, impaired motor function, epilepsy, spasticity, speech, as well as gastrointestinal and respiratory issues.\n\nWhen John was in his toddler and pre-school years, he worked hard to make developmental strides that most people take for granted.  Crawling and walking were milestones that, with therapy and determination, John achieved by the age of 4.  After enjoying his success for only a few short years, John began to experience seizures at the age of 6.  The onset of epilepsy caused John to lose skills that he had once gained such as walking, eating, and even turning pages in his books.  John now gets all of his nutrition through a G-Tube and uses a wheelchair for mobility.  John has also required frequent and lengthy hospital stays at Scottish Rite for respiratory infections and seizures. \n\nDespite the tremendous setbacks that John has experienced, he is an absolute joy to encounter! He embodies the phrase, \\u201cSunshine on a Ranney Day\\u201d because even when things seem like they couldn''t get much worse to those who love him, John''s will, determination, strength and love shine through the darkness to declare that brighter days are ahead!\n\nJoseph''s primary struggles with M2DS are developmental.  Joseph began walking just a few weeks shy of his 2nd birthday and has been on the go ever since!  Fine motor skills, such as eating and writing with utensils, have been challenging for Joseph.  He communicates non-verbally and is learning to use a picture exchange binder with the hopes of getting a communication device in the near future.  \n\nBoth John and Joseph bring so much joy to their family, friends and everyone who has the pleasure of meeting them.  Their older sister, A.J., is their favorite person in the world and their favorite activities include taking walks to the lake and riding in the golf cart.  John and Joseph are overcomers who know that life is not a race where the finish line is at the end but rather, it is a celebration of what one has achieved at the end of each day!","quote":"John and Joseph are overcomers who know that life is not a race where the finish line is at the end but rather, it is a celebration of what one has achieved at the end of each day!","heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/hero/public","photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-01/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-02/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-03/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-04/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-05/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-06/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-07/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-08/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-09/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-10/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-11/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-12/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-13/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-14/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-15/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-16/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-17/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-18/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-19/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-20/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-21/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-22/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-23/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-24/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-25/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-26/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-27/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-28/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/john-and-joseph/photo-29/public","alt":""}],"photoCount":29,"videoUrl":"https://youtu.be/Z-RTxyOWN_I","photographer":"Nicole Wood Photography","partnerLogos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/donors/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/cobb-emc-foundation/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/beruna-restoration/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/randall-brothers/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/american-signature-furniture/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/traditions-in-tile/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/schluter-systems/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/delta-faucet/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/pulleyassociates/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/devore-johnson/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/tko-plumbing-2023/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/servicewise-electric/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/bin-there-dump-that/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/nicole-photography/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/nothing-bundt-cakes/public"}],"shortDescription":null,"metaDescription":null,"altTexts":null,"jsonLd":null,"streamVideoId":"67bc2f80c2b8e659385e0edf6c06e8e0","childCount":2,"roomCount":2}');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('jonah', 'Jonah', 2019, 'completed', 0, 1, 1, '{"name":"Jonah","slug":"jonah","age":6,"diagnosis":"Heart Defect","roomTypes":["Therapy Room"],"year":2019,"status":"completed","bio":"Jonah was hospitalized for twenty-eight days. They were able to monitor him and discovered that he had Hypoplastic Right Heart Syndrome (HRHS), pulmonary stenosis, subaortic stenosis, bicuspid aortic valve and an atrioventricular septal defect.\n\nHe had kidney surgery at two and a half years old. In June of 2017, Jonah had his third stage heart surgery called the Fontan. Jonah will more than likely undergo another heart intervention in the future. Jonah had his tonsils and adenoids removed in June 2018 and will undergo another palate surgery in August 2018 to correct velopharyngeal incompetence. He is ready to take on all of these procedures with the spirit of a true warrior. Currently, Jonah is considered nonverbal, but is gaining momentum daily in speech. Jonah has a device to communicate, however most often he chooses to use words and sign language to make his needs known. Jonah loves going to school, doing hippotherapy at McKenna Farms, visiting the library and hanging out at Barnes & Nobles. He is a bright child that is willing to help with any chore whether it is yardwork, laundry or unloading the dishwasher washer. Jonah has been a fighter from day one. When doctors tell us that Jonah will not be able to do something, he defies the odds and proves them wrong. They told us that Jonah wouldn''t crawl or walk, but he did! He was tube-fed for years, but after participating in an intensive therapeutic feeding program at Marcus Feeding Clinic, he can now eat any food he wants and drink from cups. Jonah proves that where there is a will, there is a way! He is full of heart and vigor. Despite the challenges he has faced, Jonah''s radiant smile and infectious laughter have both remained constant. Sunshine on a Ranney Day wants to see more of his brilliant smiles and that''s why we can''t wait to finish his dream therapy room makeover! We''d love to have you join us at the unveiling of his newly redesigned therapy room!","quote":"Jonah was hospitalized for twenty-eight days. They were able to monitor him and discovered that he had Hypoplastic Right Heart Syndrome (HRHS), pulmonary stenosis, subaortic stenosis, bicuspid aortic valve and an atrioventricular septal defect.","heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/hero/public","photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-01/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-02/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-03/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-04/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-05/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-06/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-07/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-08/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-09/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-10/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-11/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-12/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-13/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-14/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jonah/photo-15/pub