-tile-design/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/niki-murphy-photography/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/the-town-carpenter/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/atlas-disposal/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/united-site-services/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/cr-construction-v2/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/premier-anesthesia/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/ian-hunter/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/roswell-womens-club/public"}],"shortDescription":null,"metaDescription":null,"altTexts":null,"jsonLd":null,"_migration":{"scrapedAt":"2026-03-06T13:32:09.411Z","source":"wordpress-xml-export","wpPostDate":"2018-03-27 23:06:16","wpCategories":["Meet the Kids"],"wpTags":["2018","Accessible Bathroom"],"thumbnailId":6889,"needsReview":[],"cfHeroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/6b7f10a1-2cc7-43e5-206d-8b87fc093800/full"},"streamVideoId":"cccb6f4de1c340b619e33898918f246c","roomCount":1}');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('peter', 'Peter', 2026, 'in-progress', 0, 1, 2, '{"name":"Peter","slug":"peter","age":14,"diagnosis":"Leigh''s Disease","roomTypes":["Accessible Bathroom","Dream Bedroom"],"year":2026,"status":"in-progress","bio":"Peter was adopted from Russia when he was just over a year old. Peter has always had a natural charisma and an infectious happiness that draws people to him, so full of joy that even the adoption judge remarked on his remarkable personality.\n\nWhen Peter was two years old, he suffered a stroke. After further testing, he was diagnosed with Leigh''s disease, a rare and progressive neurological disorder that affects the body''s ability to produce energy at the cellular level. Over time, the condition gradually robs individuals of strength, mobility, and independence. Peter has experienced additional strokes, and as the disease progresses, more daily functions become challenging.\n\nToday, Peter is wheelchair-dependent. As he grows into his teenage years, he longs for greater independence—something every young person desires. At the same time, his parents are thoughtfully planning for the future, knowing his needs will continue to increase as they themselves grow older.\n\nDespite everything he faces, Peter''s spirit remains bright. He loves the police and proudly says he wants to become a police officer when he \\u201cgrows up.\\u201d His determination, courage, and enduring joy continue to inspire everyone around him.","quote":null,"heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peter/hero/public","photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/jackson/photo-01/public","alt":""}],"photoCount":1,"videoUrl":null,"photographer":null,"partnerLogos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/kids-r-kids/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/real-floors-commercial/public"},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/partners/wyp/public"}],"shortDescription":null,"metaDescription":null,"altTexts":null,"jsonLd":null,"roomCount":2}');
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO kids (slug, name, year, status, featured, child_count, room_count, data) VALUES ('peyton', 'Peyton', 2023, 'completed', 0, 1, 2, '{"name":"Peyton","slug":"peyton","age":7,"diagnosis":"Cerebral Palsy, Hydrocephalus, Epilepsy","roomTypes":["Accessible Bathroom","Dream Bedroom"],"year":2023,"status":"completed","bio":"In 2015, Crystal gave birth to twins Peyton and Taylor at 26 weeks. Both only weighed a little over a pound a piece! Taylor had a brain bleed and Peyton suffered bilateral brain bleeds grade 3 and 4. After both came down with hydrocephalus, the girls got a VP shunt to help drain extra cerebrospinal fluid from the brain. All of this resulted in 3 months in the NICU! For the first year of their lives afterward, all seemed normal until they noticed Peyton was ignoring her right hand. They soon began early interventions and before long Peyton was diagnosed with cerebral palsy, affecting the right side of her body. She worked super hard in therapies and was able to take her first steps at 3 years old! Since then, Peyton began having seizures and now has the diagnosis of focal epilepsy as well.\n\nDespite everything she has gone through, she is the sweetest, happiest girl! In June of 2022 she underwent a surgery called selective dorsal rhizotomy at Children''s Healthcare of Atlanta. This surgery was intended to relieve some of her symptoms of cerebral palsy and hopefully help her stay mobile and gain more skills. Peyton spent 30 days in the rehab facility at the hospital, working through intensive physical therapy. Even though this surgery requires a lot out of Peyton for the first year post-op, she has stayed so joyful and determined! Her hard work of relearning how to walk again paid off when she took her first independent steps again a week before Halloween. She attends intensive physical therapy 5 days a week and is making great strides towards a full recovery! \\u201cShe is truly my hero,\\u201d - Peyton''s mom, Crystal.","quote":"\"Despite everything she has gone through, she is the sweetest, happiest girl!\"","heroImage":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/hero/public","photos":[{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-01/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-02/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-03/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-04/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-05/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-06/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-07/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-08/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-09/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-10/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-11/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-12/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-13/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-14/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-15/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-16/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-17/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-18/public","alt":""},{"url":"https://imagedelivery.net/ROYFuPmfN2vPS6mt5sCkZQ/kids/peyton/photo-19/public","alt":""}